- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper compares feature-based and neural network-based models for the task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated processing of natural language. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper includes experiments with neural network-based models. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch upon societal implications of automated natural language processing.
